wordplay
------------------------------------------
Wordplay is a game for Unix/GTK+. It is primarily aimed at Scrabble(TM)
players looking to improve their anagramming and hooking skills, but can
also be played for fun. The dictionary used is the full TWL98 word list
(used for tournaments and club play in the U.S. and Canada).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  gdk-pixbuf-0.22.0-5
  glib-1.2.10-3
  gtk+-1.2.10-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.5-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1

Canonical website and download:
  http://ironphoenix.org/tril/wordplay/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack wordplay-0.3-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./wordplay-0.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/wordplay-0.3-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/wordplay-0.3-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

